================================================================================
REVIEWED SUMMARY
================================================================================

C++ header:         include/emTreeDump/emTreeDumpFileModel.h
C++ implementation: src/emTreeDump/emTreeDumpFileModel.cpp

Purpose: emRecFileModel subclass that loads a saved .emTreeDump file
into an emTreeDumpRec tree, suitable for consumption by
emTreeDumpFilePanel as the model half of the in-app renderer's
model/panel pair. Acquired via the context registry keyed by file
path, shared across panels viewing the same file.

Status: NOT PORTED — in-app dump-renderer subsystem out of scope for
the current dump-producer work (Phase 1 of
docs/superpowers/specs/2026-04-24-treedump-port-design.md).

The Rust port has no model that loads .emTreeDump files for in-app
rendering. Nothing in the Rust port references emTreeDumpFileModel
or would consume its output — the producer-only work lands in
emTreeDump.rs and writes files that C++ Eagle Mode (or a future Rust
renderer port) can open.

Rust equivalent for now: none. No file-model type exists for this
format in the Rust port.

Future port path: paired with emTreeDumpFilePanel; ports together
if/when the in-app dump viewer is ported. Depends on emTreeDumpRec
being ported first so the model has a typed tree to populate.
